# Production API origin the built SPA calls. Leave empty to use same-origin "/api"
# (e.g. when the SPA is served behind a reverse proxy that forwards /api to the API).
# In local dev this is ignored — Vite proxies /api to the backend (see vite.config.ts).
VITE_API_BASE_URL=

# Optional: override the dev proxy target if the API runs somewhere other than http://localhost:5002
# VITE_DEV_API_TARGET=http://localhost:5002

# Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD) SSO — optional. Leave both blank to keep SSO disabled; the
# login screen falls back to a friendly "not configured, use guest" message.
# Get these from your Azure Portal → App registrations → your SPA app:
#   VITE_AZURE_AD_TENANT_ID  = Directory (tenant) ID
#   VITE_AZURE_AD_CLIENT_ID  = Application (client) ID
# The SPA requests the scope `api://<clientId>/access_as_user` — add that scope under
# "Expose an API" in the same App registration.
VITE_AZURE_AD_TENANT_ID=
VITE_AZURE_AD_CLIENT_ID=
